				<wikidot:authorName>ghoulfriend</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2540662</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is disgusting and I like it a lot.</p> <p>Small quibble about the following sentence, though: &quot;They are to be fed intravenously, and a system of <strong>colonoscopy bags</strong> &amp; urea catheters has been set up to capture any resulting waste.&quot; If you intended &quot;colonoscopy bag&quot; as it stands, please disregard, but I see this error a lot - in medical documentation we would refer to what I think you're describing as an &quot;ostomy bag&quot; or a &quot;colostomy bag&quot;.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
