					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13168059#post-4557372</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13168059/scp-5207#post-4557372</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 20 Mar 2020 21:58:34 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>SoullessSingularity</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>637830</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>separated to give the subject large round ears</p> </blockquote> <p>You want to put in a comma between two adjectives describing the same noun. Otherwise you are implying that &quot;large&quot; is an performing an adverb onto &quot;round&quot;.</p> <blockquote> <p>which now displays</p> </blockquote> <p>You don't need 'now' here</p> <blockquote> <p>extends some significant distance from the anus.</p> </blockquote> <p>I would love an exact measurement here because it implies someone got a ruler.</p> <p>Overall I'm sitting on it, not sure if I like it as a standalone object yet. Excellent imagery.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
